<topic id="custom-refactoring-operations">
  <title>Custom Refactoring Operations</title>
  <body>
    <p>If none of the predefined operations will help you accomplish a particular refactoring task,
      you can create a custom operation that is specific to your needs. For example, if you want to
      convert an attribute to an element and insert the element as the first child of the parent
      element, a custom refactoring operation needs to be created.</p>
    <p>An XML Refactoring operation is defined
      <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T164615+0200" content="with two resources"?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T164618+0200"?>as
      a pair of two resources<?oxy_insert_end?>:<ul id="ul_gwv_s4c_jr">
        <li><?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T165716+0200" content="An &lt;i&gt;XQuery Update&lt;/i&gt; script file that needs to be processed to refactor XML files."?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T165601+0200"?>An
          XQuery Update script file that oXygen will run in order to refactor XML
          files.<?oxy_insert_end?></li>
        <li>An <i><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T164707+0200"?>XML
            <?oxy_insert_end?>Operation Descriptor</i> file that contains information about the
          operation, such as the name, description, and parameters.</li>
      </ul><fig id="fig_dgt_f4c_jr">
        <title>Diagram of an XML Refactoring Operation</title>
        <image href="../img/refactoring_diagram1.png" id="image_ktw_k4c_jr"/>
      </fig></p>
    <p>All the defined operations are loaded by the XML Refactoring tool and presented in <xref
        href="xml-refactoring-tool.dita#xml-refactoring-tool/refactoring_operations_dlentry">the
          <uicontrol>Refactoring operations</uicontrol>
        <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T165343+0200" content="dialog box"?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T165344+0200"?>wizard
        page<?oxy_insert_end?></xref>. </p>
    <p>After the user chooses an operation and specifies its parameters, an XQuery
      <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T165625+0200" content="u"?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T165625+0200"?>U<?oxy_insert_end?>pdate
      transformation is processed over the input file. This transformation is executed in a
        <term>safe mode</term>, which implies the
      following:<?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T170405+0200" type="split"?></p>
    <p><?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T170421+0200"?>When
      loading the document:<?oxy_insert_end?></p>
    <?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T171230+0200"?>
    <ul id="ul_mfj_dqc_jr">
      <li>The XInclude mechanism is disabled. This means that the resources included by using
        XInclude will not be visible in the transformation.</li>
      <li>The DTD entities will be processed without being expanded.</li>
      <li>The associated DTD will be not loaded, so the default attributes declared in the DTD will
        not be visible in the transformation.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>When saving the updated XML document:</p>
    <ul id="ul_kl5_ysz_jr">
      <li>The <codeph>DOCTYPE</codeph> will be preserved.</li>
      <li>The DTD entities will be preserved as they are in the original document when the document
        is saved.</li>
      <li>The attribute values will be kept in their original form without being normalized.</li>
      <li>The spaces between attributes are preserved. Basically, the spaces are lost by an XML
        serialization since they are not considered important.</li>
    </ul>
    <?oxy_insert_end?>
    <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150316T171736+0200" content="&lt;p&gt;&lt;ul id=&quot;ul_mfj_dqc_jr&quot;/&gt;&lt;ul id=&quot;ul_kl5_ysz_jr&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;The &lt;codeph&gt;DOCTYPE&lt;/codeph&gt; will be preserved.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The entities will be preserved.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The attribute values will be kept in their original form without being normalized.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The spaces between attributes are preserved. Basically, the spaces are lost by an XML serialization since they are not considered important.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"?>
    <p>The result of this transformation overrides the initial input file.</p>
    <section>
      <title>Creating a Custom Refactoring Operation</title>
      <p>To create a custom refactoring operation, follow these steps:<ol id="ol_swm_crc_jr">
          <li><xref href="custom-refactoring-xquery-script.dita">Create
              a<?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T094537+0200"?>n<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T094540+0200" content=" custom"?>
              XQuery <?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T094544+0200"?>Update
              <?oxy_insert_end?>script file</xref>.</li>
          <li><xref href="xml-refactoring-operation-descriptor.dita">Create a<?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T094628+0200"?>n<?oxy_insert_end?>
              <?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T094631+0200"?><b>XML
                Refactoring Operation Descriptor</b>
              <?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T094647+0200" content="custom operation Descriptor "?>file</xref>.</li>
          <li><?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T095229+0200" content="Copy both files to the &lt;i&gt;refactoring&lt;/i&gt; folder in the application installation directory (&lt;filepath&gt;[oXygen Installation Directory]/refactoring/&lt;/filepath&gt;). "?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T095247+0200"?>Copy
            both files in <xref
              href="sharing-custom-refactoring-operations.dita#sharing-custom-refactoring-operations"
              >one of the folders scanned by <ph keyref="product"/></xref> when it loads the custom
              operations.<?oxy_insert_end?><p><?oxy_comment_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T095146+0200" comment="This should be moved outside the ul element because is not part of the procedure."?>Once
              you
              <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150318T093127+0200" content="restart"?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150318T093128+0200"?>run
              again<?oxy_insert_end?> the <uicontrol>XML Refactoring</uicontrol> tool, the custom
              operation appears in <xref
                href="xml-refactoring-tool.dita#xml-refactoring-tool/refactoring_operations_dlentry"
                >the <uicontrol>Refactoring operations</uicontrol>
                <?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T101517+0200" content="dialog box"?><?oxy_insert_start author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T101517+0200"?>wizard
                page<?oxy_insert_end?></xref>.<?oxy_comment_end?></p></li>
        </ol></p>
    </section>
    <p><?oxy_delete author="radu_pisoi" timestamp="20150317T101411+0200" content="There are also several mechanisms to &lt;xref href=&quot;sharing-custom-refactoring-operations.dita&quot;&gt;share custom refactoring operations&lt;/xref&gt; with other members of your team."?></p>
